Browse an exciting collection of scientific, historical and cultural facts about space, galaxies, the planets and other objects in the solar system. The latest discoveries, space-related features, graphics and diagrams can be found on the blog.Start exploring below:Space is the area beyond the upper limits of Earth’s atmosphere. It is where all of the asteroids, comets, planets, stars, solar systems and galaxies in our universe are found. Space is a vacuum, meaning it contains almost nothing, but it is not completely empty.